body:
* Revamped Group management, filtering and editing, support for changing icons, renaming, deleting.
* MacOS: Fixed font for older MacOS Versions

* Support for Microsoft OneDrive (#71)
* Improved Authorization flow for Dropbox.
* Allow customizing of visual density and font scale.
* TOTP: Disable OTP secret padding (makes it more compatible with e.g. GitHub, Amazon, etc.)
* TOTP: Fix barcode scanner (missing camera permissions)

* Added support for file attachments/binaries.
* Filter by groups, show/hide deleted trash items, etc.
* Fix reading/writing timestamps correctly.
* Fix compatibility problems with kdbx 4 timestamps.
* Correctly display modification timestamp in local time zone.

name: Critical bug fix release
body: * Critical bugfix, Error opening files with missing Recycle Bin.

* By default hide recycle bin/deleted items, allow changing of filter by group.
* Add `Help` menu item to open https://authpass.app/docs/
* Fix potential bug in argon2 hashing.

* Android: Add file handler to open  *.kdbx files.
* Android/iOS: Improved opening of existing files through document picker APIs.
  * Previously changes were not correctly persisted back to the original location.
* Android: Improved autofill username/password field detection.
* fixed appbar menu not refreshing correctly.

* Allow changing of database name.
* Large Screens (Tablet/Desktop): Improved responsiveness of search box.
* Update flutter dependency to 1.17 (beta).
* Fixed potential crash on iOS file picker. 
  https://github.com/miguelpruivo/flutter_file_picker/issues/200
* Decryption: Improved performance and fixed potential crash
  for larger kdbx files.

* Initial support for kdbx 4.x (Keepass 2.x) with argon2.
* Fixed bugs/compatibility with keyfiles in hex and base64 formats.

* Added dark mode - either through configuration, or taken from android 10 or ios 13 system.
* Show groups/categories of password entries
* Allow basic management of groups/categories.
* Added built-in way to send log file via email to support. (Android, iOS)

* Add support for 2fa (2nd Factor Authentication) based on Time-based One Time Passwords (TOTP).
* A couple of bug fixes and improvements to error messages.

![authpass-onetime-token-totp](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/313066/73727531-f190f500-4731-11ea-9ad3-51a406e6fa2c.gif)

More details [on the release blog post](https://authpass.app/articles/android-password-autofill-webdav-owncloud-nextcloud/) ;-)

* Android: Auto-Fill Support (Implements basic support using android Autofill Support Since Android 8.0, Oreo)
* Support for WebDAV (e.g. for using with NextCloud, OwnCloud)
* Many other usability fixes ;-)

![authpass-autofill-android-device-2019-10-07-225627 2019-10-07 23_05_12](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/313066/66349075-58ef9180-e958-11e9-9a84-a9848fc648d7.gif)

* Support for opening multiple database vaults/kdbx at the same time.
* Assign color labels to each open database to easily separate which passwords are in which file.
* Improved password entry detail list.
* Better highlight username/password fields when copying to clipboard.
* Improved Dropbox support: Make sure files have not been modified by another machine during saving.
* Added UI for managing open database files (Saving in another storage, renaming, assigning color labels, etc.)
* Added configurable password generator
* Now also available from [f-droid](https://f-droid.org/en/packages/design.codeux.authpass.fdroid/)
* Android: [Google Play Store](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=design.codeux.authpass&referrer=utm_source%3Dgithub_release) [F-Droid](https://f-droid.org/en/packages/design.codeux.authpass.fdroid/)
* MacOS: [Mac App Store](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=design.codeux.authpass&referrer=utm_source%3Dgithub&at=11l8ru) (or download directly from github)
* iOS: [iOS App Store](https://apps.apple.com/app/authpass-password-manager/id1479297675?ls=1&at=11l8ru)

name: v1.0.2
body:
* UI Improvements for small(er) screens.
* Improved kdbx 2.x compatibility.
* iOS/MacOS: Added support for fingerprints (Android already had it in 1.0.0)
* MacOS: Fix bug opening file outside the App Sandbox

name: Initial Release (Mac Desktop, Android, iOS)
body:
The first release! For Mac Desktop, Android and iOS!

* Manage all passwords
  * Basic support for Searching passwords (custom fields, protected fields, changing of icons ,etc.)
* Read & Store & Create Keepass kdbx 2.x Files (with Password, Keyfile not yet supported)
* Responsive design to make two columns for desktop and tablet
* Show fields/passwords as large HUD and QR Code for simple sharing

Also [available in the desktop Mac App Store](https://apps.apple.com/app/authpass-password-manager/id1478552452?ls=1&mt=12)
